genresAdvancedInfo.name: polynesian traditional
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Polynesian traditional music is a genre that encompasses the traditional music of the Polynesian islands, including Hawaii, Samoa, Tonga, and Tahiti. It is characterized by the use of traditional instruments such as the ukulele, conch shells, and drums, as well as vocal harmonies and storytelling through song.
